1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:02,467
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:04,167 --> 00:00:06,533
I'm not asking
for instant forgiveness.

3
00:00:06,667 --> 00:00:07,967
What I'm asking

4
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:09,400
is a chance to earn it.

5
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:11,300
Marj, can we start over again?

6
00:00:11,433 --> 00:00:12,533
Thea and I are together.

7
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:15,367
Do you regret letting me go?

8
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,933
Ever since we separated,
I've had peace of mind.

9
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:19,933
Edward seems completely
disgusted with you.

10
00:00:20,067 --> 00:00:23,167
And if you want him to feel
the pain, give me a call.

11
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:27,133
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

12
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:48,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

13
00:01:13,467 --> 00:01:15,367
- [GRUMBLES]
- Edward!

14
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:18,567
You're so hard to get!

15
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:22,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

16
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:29,233
Thea?

17
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,800
Thea Torrecampo?

18
00:01:37,233 --> 00:01:39,033
What are you doing here alone?

19
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:42,333
I'm celebrating the death
of my marriage.

20
00:01:45,067 --> 00:01:46,700
Wait.

21
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:51,067
Aren't you Mr. Vien Ledesma?

22
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:54,533
A board member
of Torrecampo Realty?

23
00:01:57,733 --> 00:01:58,767
Yeah.

24
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:10,100
You really reserved this place
for us?

25
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:13,867
It's beautiful.

26
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:17,033
You're beautiful.

27
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,533
You're so corny.

28
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:22,133
[CHUCKLES]

29
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,833
Are you courting me?

30
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,767
What else do you think
I'm doing...

31
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,233
Miss Tough?

32
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,233
Now we're talking.

33
00:02:35,267 --> 00:02:36,567
I'm surprised

34
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:37,967
you remember me.

35
00:02:39,467 --> 00:02:41,333
But what are we doing here?

36
00:02:41,467 --> 00:02:43,900
Do the board members still have
a meeting?

37
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:45,633
- [CHUCKLES]
- No,

38
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:47,367
I'm here for myself.

39
00:02:49,067 --> 00:02:51,633
And I heard what happened
to you

40
00:02:51,767 --> 00:02:53,000
with your husband.

41
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,167
And I must say,

42
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,500
he made a huge mistake

43
00:02:58,633 --> 00:02:59,867
to let you go.

44
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:01,900
Just look at you.

45
00:03:03,033 --> 00:03:05,533
You look absolutely perfect.

46
00:03:05,667 --> 00:03:06,833
You look amazing.

47
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:12,067
Marj, I know I don't
deserve a second chance.

48
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,433
With all my faults,

49
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:18,067
and all the times I hurt you.

50
00:03:19,133 --> 00:03:20,600
But when you almost drowned,

51
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,467
that's when I realized

52
00:03:23,667 --> 00:03:25,600
I couldn't lose you.

53
00:03:27,167 --> 00:03:29,000
That was very inappropriate
what I said.

54
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:30,967
No.

55
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:32,233
It's all right.

56
00:03:35,267 --> 00:03:36,633
Actually,

57
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:40,367
I was flattered
that's how you see me.

58
00:03:56,967 --> 00:03:58,100
I know

59
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:01,200
it's a long shot.

60
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,067
But I'll still fight for it.

61
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:08,167
And I will never give up
our marriage.

62
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:12,533
So even if I have to court
you every day,

63
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,767
just to regain your trust,

64
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,933
I'll do it.

65
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:21,567
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:31,100
Marj,

67
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:36,467
I'm not asking
for instant forgiveness.

68
00:04:37,767 --> 00:04:39,267
What I'm asking

69
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,433
is a chance to earn it.

70
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:46,300
One chance

71
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,300
to be your spouse again.

72
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:54,467
And a father worthy of Jasmine
and Ashley.

73
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,700
So, Marj,

74
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,233
I only have one question
for you.

75
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:04,967
My love,

76
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:07,967
my Miss Tough,

77
00:05:10,267 --> 00:05:11,933
can we start over again?

78
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:15,000
[OST MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:05:20,067 --> 00:05:21,667
I can't promise

80
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:24,633
things will go back right away.

81
00:05:26,933 --> 00:05:30,033
You know wounds don't heal
easily like that.

82
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,633
A lot was broken.

83
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:36,867
A lot needs fixing.

84
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:42,667
I'm willing to give you
a chance.

85
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:47,067
Marj,

86
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:49,733
thank you.

87
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:53,800
I promise

88
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:55,500
I won't fail you again.

89
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:05,900
[OST MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:30,700
I'll go ahead ah.

91
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:32,933
I'll see you next Tuesday.

92
00:06:33,067 --> 00:06:34,633
Or maybe not.

93
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,867
What's the problem?

94
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,167
Is your allowance short?

95
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:45,467
Do you want to go shopping?

96
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:48,133
What is it?

97
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:50,400
That's not all I need!

98
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:52,500
I mean, look at us.

99
00:06:52,633 --> 00:06:54,033
Every time we see each other,

100
00:06:54,167 --> 00:06:55,967
it's always at a hotel.

101
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:56,967
Why?

102
00:06:57,100 --> 00:07:00,233
What? Are you embarrassed to
display me?

103
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:02,967
What's wrong with people
seeing us?

104
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:04,433
You're single anyway,

105
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:06,467
and Edward and I are separated.

106
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:09,467
Not yet legally, but consensual.

107
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,200
I feel like

108
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,567
I'm a mistress again.

109
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,600
I've been there already.

110
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:18,833
I don't want to go back there.

111
00:07:18,967 --> 00:07:20,767
I'm tired of hiding again.

112
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:29,500
Is something funny?

113
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,200
You talk too much.

114
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,767
You're so dramatic.

115
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:39,033
So you just want me
to hard launch you.

116
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:42,733
We have a lunch meeting
tomorrow.

117
00:07:44,033 --> 00:07:45,400
I want you to come with me.

118
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:48,433
Will Edward be there?

119
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:51,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:53,267
So, I guess we're settled here,

121
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,400
right?

122
00:07:58,067 --> 00:08:01,933
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

123
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:12,267
What are you doing here, Thea?

124
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,667
I meant to tell you sooner,
Edward.

125
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,533
But there was no chance.

126
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:21,000
I guess it's quite obvious.

127
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,733
Thea and I are together.

128
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,533
You're separated anyway, right?

129
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:28,333
So, I guess we don't have
a problem.

130
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:29,967
Oh,

131
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,933
that's fine.

132
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:35,267
Edward doesn't care anymore.

133
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:37,467
Right, Edward?

134
00:08:40,433 --> 00:08:42,233
I'm impressed, Thea.

135
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:44,267
We just broke up

136
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,900
and you recovered so fast.

137
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,967
Hey,

138
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,767
you're jealous, aren't you?

139
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:55,200
Do you regret letting me go?

140
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:58,733
Why would I regret it?

141
00:09:00,467 --> 00:09:02,667
Ever since we separated,

142
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,367
I've never felt free.

143
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,400
Now, I finally have peace
of mind.

144
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:10,733
So to answer your question,
Mr. Ledesma,

145
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:12,533
we won't have any problem.

146
00:09:12,667 --> 00:09:14,600
Thea is all yours

147
00:09:14,733 --> 00:09:17,333
because I have no plans to get
back with her.

148
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:22,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,067
Let's go. Let's leave!

150
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:34,267
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:43,533
Damn it!

152
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,100
He thinks he's something!

153
00:09:45,233 --> 00:09:49,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:09:53,733 --> 00:09:55,667
You must feel awful.

155
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,667
Your plan backfired.

156
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:00,233
What are you talking about?

157
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:04,733
I wouldn't be successful
in business

158
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:06,900
if I weren't good
at reading people.

159
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:11,067
I know you only went along
with Vien

160
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,833
not just to survive,

161
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,700
but to make Edward jealous.

162
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:17,867
Isn't that right?

163
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:21,567
Admit it, Thea.

164
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,400
You're still hoping

165
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:26,300
for your husband
to ask you back.

166
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:30,300
But the plan didn't work.

167
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:33,133
[CHUCKLES]

168
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:35,967
It looks like Edward
is disgusted with you.

169
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:40,900
Are you bored?

170
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:43,767
That's why you're meddling
in my life too?

171
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:47,100
Can you please just mind
your own business.

172
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:50,667
Look, Thea.

173
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,867
You're just trash

174
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,333
and worthless to Edward.

175
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:59,067
But to me,

176
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,433
you're useful.

177
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:04,033
So if you change your mind

178
00:11:06,167 --> 00:11:07,800
and if you want to get even
with your husband

179
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:09,700
for taking everything from you,

180
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:12,200
and if you want him to feel
the pain

181
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:13,933
that you're feeling right now,

182
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:16,067
give me a call.

183
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:20,200
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:11:25,167 --> 00:11:29,833
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:52,100
Careful, Grandfather.

186
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:53,700
Thank you, Dear.

187
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:56,667
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:08,267
Dad,

189
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,367
Jas.

190
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:13,167
Marj and I already talked.

191
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:17,467
We talked last night and,

192
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,633
well,

193
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:22,433
we have decided to give our
marriage another chance.

194
00:12:24,133 --> 00:12:25,000
Really, Dad?

195
00:12:25,133 --> 00:12:26,000
Yeah.

196
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:29,133
Finally, my prayers
have been answered.

197
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:32,333
Aside from my recovery,
that's all I keep asking God

198
00:12:32,467 --> 00:12:35,000
to please bring you and Mommy
back together.

199
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,933
One day at a time, my child.

200
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:40,467
This isn't magic that things
instantly become okay.

201
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:45,167
Like your dad said, there's no
guarantee it will be easy.

202
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,267
But we'll try.

203
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:50,167
For you and for the two of us.

204
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,767
Thank you, Mommy.

205
00:12:57,867 --> 00:12:59,167
Thank you, Dad.

206
00:13:01,167 --> 00:13:03,033
This is the best news ever.

207
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:04,133
[CHUCKLES]

208
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:07,600
At least

209
00:13:07,733 --> 00:13:09,600
you managed to save
your marriage.

210
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:13,500
Regina and I, it seems hopeless.

211
00:13:14,667 --> 00:13:17,500
I've made too many mistakes.

212
00:13:18,533 --> 00:13:22,267
No apology can erase them.

213
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:24,700
Dad,

214
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:27,600
please don't lose hope.

215
00:13:27,733 --> 00:13:29,667
Look at Edward.

216
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:33,867
His anger toward you before was
intense, but he forgave you.

217
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,100
Because he saw your sincerity.

218
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,833
If he could do that with Edward,

219
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:43,300
it's not impossible for Mom's
heart to soften too.

220
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,433
You really think so?

221
00:13:48,267 --> 00:13:50,000
Yes, Dad.

222
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:51,833
You know, for us women,

223
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:54,867
that's one of the most
important things.

224
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:57,233
When someone who hurt us

225
00:13:57,367 --> 00:14:00,000
acknowledges their fault and
admits their mistake

226
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:01,667
and apologizes.

227
00:14:02,767 --> 00:14:04,633
Sure, it may take time,

228
00:14:04,767 --> 00:14:08,400
but we eventually learn
to forgive

229
00:14:08,533 --> 00:14:11,900
when we see that you truly
regret it.

230
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:15,767
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,000
Thank you.

232
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:34,367
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

233
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:39,267
Do I need to fill that up there?

234
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,900
Oh, okay, okay.

235
00:14:41,033 --> 00:14:42,533
My child, just wait a bit, okay?

236
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:43,833
Okay.

237
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:53,500
My child!

238
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,067
Mom?

239
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,467
Leave us for a moment.

240
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:04,033
What are you doing here, Mom?

241
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,367
You're not allowed here,
Dad might catch you.

242
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,800
I don't care.

243
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:09,667
You're all I want now.

244
00:15:09,933 --> 00:15:11,933
I'll take you away, my child.

245
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:13,933
I have someone new now.

246
00:15:14,067 --> 00:15:16,667
He's rich and he can support us.

247
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,267
He can take us
to a faraway place

248
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:22,600
where we won't be found by your
dad and the Torrecampos.

249
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:24,767
They won't be able to separate
us anymore.

250
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,867
Mom, my answer is still no.

251
00:15:27,933 --> 00:15:29,100
I don't want to go with you.

252
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,933
I'm not coming with you.

253
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,333
My child, I can accept

254
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,300
that everyone turned
their back on me,

255
00:15:37,467 --> 00:15:39,733
but are you going to reject me
too as well?

256
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:42,833
Don't you love me anymore?

257
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:45,733
Mom, I love you.

258
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:47,800
I love you very much.

259
00:15:49,233 --> 00:15:51,000
But not like this.

260
00:15:52,033 --> 00:15:55,733
I want you to fix
your mistakes first.

261
00:15:56,767 --> 00:15:58,933
I want you to change, Mom.

262
00:15:59,067 --> 00:16:00,467
[SOBBING]

263
00:16:01,733 --> 00:16:02,867
[EXHALES]

264
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:05,800
What you mean is,

265
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:08,100
you're rejecting me

266
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:11,067
because your dad poisoned
your mind.

267
00:16:13,167 --> 00:16:14,133
Why?

268
00:16:14,267 --> 00:16:16,967
Why do you prefer him over me?

269
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,300
Please stop, Mom.

270
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:19,833
Enough.

271
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:20,833
No.

272
00:16:22,067 --> 00:16:23,000
Your dad is a loser.

273
00:16:23,133 --> 00:16:24,800
He has no ambition.

274
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,433
I supported this family.

275
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:34,100
I worked myself to exhaustion
to secure our future.

276
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,933
And in the end,
you'll still choose him?

277
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:42,567
Thea?

278
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:45,867
What is this?

279
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,500
Who let you in here?

280
